This paper discusses detecting biases in artificial intelligence models, specifically in word embeddings and sentiment analysis predictions. This topic falls under the natural language processing and machine learning fields, which are covered by the cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG sub-categories. Additionally, the paper draws from experimental psychology, which could potentially place it in the cs.CY (computational and mathematical modeling of cognitive processes) or cs.HC (human-computer interaction) sub-categories.
